<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3518] MessageServletSupport request body does not check the content-type in an intelligent way</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3518</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The MessageServlet used for the REST interface supplied in the demo web app will not correctly use the request body of an HTTP POST request if the content-type header contains more than just the MIME type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The specification for this header indicates that there can be multiple values in this header.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Servlet container&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
